He was using Azo’s two Sumam at a little later time Hengham was to write his Samma Magna and Summa Parva, and Thomton his Summa based on the De Legibus. More than one of the numerous little legal tracts which sprang into being in the generation after Bracton was to be called a Samma. It was in the regular course of things that he should call his treatise a Summa rather than a Liber.
